1
00:00:03,841 --> 00:00:06,645
Kṛṣṇa is not …
All waves are favorable

2
00:00:06,645 --> 00:00:09,645
coming from the center
of the Infinite.

3
00:00:09,645 --> 00:00:15,725
Kṛṣṇa’s never trying 
to push me down, harm me,

4
00:00:15,725 --> 00:00:18,611
even when He’s being
apparently cruel.

5
00:00:19,052 --> 00:00:21,662
[Karma | Man is an Architect of His Own Fortune]

6
00:00:21,931 --> 00:00:26,842
So Guru Mahārāj said, “The devotee, 
who has this proper mentality …

7
00:00:26,846 --> 00:00:31,006
The child, who is defensive
with the mother and says,

8
00:00:31,006 --> 00:00:34,613
‘I didn’t do anything wrong,
why are you punishing me?’—

9
00:00:34,613 --> 00:00:37,058
that’s the child
who needs to be punished;

10
00:00:37,058 --> 00:00:40,351
whereas the child who says,
‘Mother, I was wrong,

11
00:00:40,351 --> 00:00:44,294
I did this wrong thing,
and I am ready for my punishment.’”

12
00:00:44,294 --> 00:00:46,717
He said, “That child 
doesn’t need any punishment.”

13
00:00:46,717 --> 00:00:50,221
Because they’re acknowledging 
their misbehaviour.

14
00:00:50,356 --> 00:00:52,126
But the one 
who is in denial …

15
00:00:52,170 --> 00:00:56,833
Like Guru Mahārāj says,
“So, if we are blaming others:

16
00:00:56,833 --> 00:01:01,777
other people, the environment, 
circumstances … ”

17
00:01:01,777 --> 00:01:06,107
There are so many excuses

18
00:01:06,107 --> 00:01:09,011
we can make 
for our present condition.

19
00:01:09,100 --> 00:01:11,450
He said, 
“Then, if that is your method,

20
00:01:11,450 --> 00:01:13,977
you are going to be in this world 
a long time.

21
00:01:13,977 --> 00:01:16,481
But as soon 
as you acknowledge,

22
00:01:16,550 --> 00:01:19,370
‘I alone am the culprit.

23
00:01:19,373 --> 00:01:22,230
Man is an architect 
of his own fortune—

24
00:01:22,230 --> 00:01:25,000
I’ve created 
my karmic circumstances,

25
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:28,510
I am responsible 
for whatever difficulties that I’m in,

26
00:01:28,510 --> 00:01:31,378
and whatever suffering,’”
he said,

27
00:01:31,378 --> 00:01:34,664
“Then your days in the material world
are numbered.

28
00:01:34,664 --> 00:01:36,654
They’ll be few.”

